## 1. Project Overview

The **PCOS Dashboard** is a web-based health management platform built to support three distinct groups: **patients**, **healthcare professionals**, and **system administrators**.

Its core purpose is to:

- Allow patients to self-assess their PCOS risk through a structured questionnaire powered by a machine learning model
- Visualise community-wide health trends through charts and analytics
- Enable healthcare professionals to monitor their patients' progress and add clinical notes
- Give administrators oversight of the entire platform, user accounts, and model performance

The platform is built entirely in **Python** using a framework called **Streamlit**, which turns Python scripts into interactive web pages without requiring traditional web development skills (HTML/CSS/JavaScript).

---

## 2. Technology Stack

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Web Framework | Streamlit | Renders the entire user interface as a web app |
| Database | MariaDB (MySQL-compatible) | Stores all user data, assessments, journal entries, predictions |
| Machine Learning | scikit-learn (Stacking Classifier) | Predicts PCOS risk level from questionnaire inputs |
| Charting | Plotly, Matplotlib | Interactive charts on the dashboard |
| Maps | PyDeck | Renders the specialist clinic map |
| External Research API | PubMed (NCBI E-Utilities) | Fetches live medical research articles |
| Clinic Data | OpenStreetMap Overpass API | Retrieves gynaecology clinic locations in Malaysia |
| Email | Gmail SMTP | Sends OTP (one-time password) verification codes |
| Authentication | bcrypt | Securely hashes and verifies passwords |
| Session Cookies | streamlit-cookies-controller | Remembers logged-in users across browser sessions |
| Environment Config | python-dotenv | Stores sensitive credentials (DB password, email) outside the code |

---

